rcs.community_hub_file_duplicate.you_jus.string: You just duplicated this file from the community! To get started, let us show you some of the things that make Figma special and different from other design tools.

rcs.constraints.setting_precise_constrai.string: Setting precise constraints lets you build fluid layouts to support multiple device sizes and breakpoints within the same group.

rcs.constraints.all_of_your_layers_adjus.string: All of your layers adjust the way you expect – no magic, you get full control.

rcs.export.export_your_designs_for_use_i.string: Export your designs for use in production or to share with your team.

rcs.export.figma_can_export_to_png_jpeg_.string: Figma can export to PNG, JPEG, SVG, and PDF.

rcs.live_device_preview.to_view_your_fra.string: To view your frames live on your device, just download Figma Mirror on your {linkToIOS} or {linkToAndroid} device.

rcs.live_device_preview.they_ll_update_i.string: They’ll update instantly no matter what network you’re on and with no need to connect via USB.

rcs.multiplayer.collaborate_in_real_time.string: Collaborate in real time with your team and never worry about your files being up-to-date.

rcs.multiplayer.no_syncing_no_waiting_no.string: No syncing, no waiting, no merge conflicts.

rcs.launch_nux_modal.take_a_quick_tour_o.string: Take a quick tour of Figma?

rcs.launch_nux_modal.walk_through_figma_.string: Walk through Figma’s unique editor and collaboration features.

rcs.sharing.share_your_projects_with_tea.string: Share your projects with teammates, clients, and stakeholders but don’t let them mess up your files.

rcs.sharing.control_their_access_with_gr.string: Control their access with granular permissions and manage their access in one simple place.

rcs.team_library.share_components_and_st.string: Share components and styles across your team by publishing them to the team library.

rcs.team_library.enable_quick_access_to_.string: Enable quick access to other libraries in this file.

rcs.universal_inserts.insert_components_.string: Access ready-to-use resources from the Figma Community—like reusable components, on-canvas widgets, and powerful plugins.

rcs.vector_networks.pen_tools_have_alway.string: Pen tools have always been scary to use because they can be touchy and fragile.

rcs.vector_networks.now_they_re_both_sim.string: Now, they’re both simpler and more powerful – paths finally work the way they should.

mouse_navigation_preferences_modal.exist.string: Give it a try—you can change it back by clicking on the Figma icon and going to {filePref}.
An easier way to zoom and pan

mouse_navigation_preferences_tooltip.exi.string: Change them any time by going to the Figma icon and clicking {filePref}.

dev_handoff.paywall.starter_trial_nudge..string: Bring design and development together with two free weeks of handoff tools—like annotation, advanced inspection, and more.

cursor_bot.a_frame_will_hold_the_rest_of.string: A frame will hold the rest of your design like a container. Plus, you can use it to draw rectangular UI like boxes and buttons.
